<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1912-11-21T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1912-11-21T00:00:00-05:00" n="420" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d420">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 811.34537/108a.</note>
                        <head ana="#head_untitled-inferred-from-preceding-sibling-head">[Untitled]</head>
                        <opener>
                            <seg rendition="#left">No. 170.]</seg>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>, <lb/>
                                    <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1912-11-21">
                                    <hi rend="italic">November 21, 1912</hi></date>.</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: Referring to previous correspondence on
                            the subject, I enclose a full power<note n="1" xml:id="d420fn1">Not
                                printed.</note> authorizing you to sign with the Government of Cuba
                            an agreement amending the agreements between the United States and Cuba
                            concluded February 16/23, 1903, and July 2, 1903, by which certain
                            described areas of land and water in Guantánamo and Bahía Honda were
                            leased to the United States for the purpose of coaling and naval
                            stations.</p>
                        <p>I am [etc.]</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">P. C. Knox</hi>.</signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>